Drive through the ball of your foot extending your knees until youre upright and standing on the box.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-barbell-reverse-step-up-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-bodyweight-reverse-step-up-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Barbell Side Step Up', 'Start by standing with your feet about hip-width apart, with a barbell on your shoulders. Your feet should be slightly pointed outward, and your shoulders should be down and relaxed.
Place a step or box beside you, and step up onto it with one foot. Your other foot should remain on the ground.
Push off your grounded foot, raising your body up onto the step.
Step back down with the same foot, returning to the starting position.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-barbell-side-step-up-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-barbell-side-step-up-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Barbell Split Squat', 'Take a large step forward with one leg, and lower your body until your back knee nearly touches the ground. Your front knee should be bent at a 90-degree angle, and your back leg should be straight.
Push through the heel of your front foot to raise your body back to the starting position.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-barbell-split-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-barbell-split-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Barbell Step Up Balance', 'Begin by standing in front of a sturdy box or bench that is about knee-height, holding a barbell across your upper back and shoulders, using an overhand grip.
