Go down until your thighs are parallel to the floor, then pause for a moment.
Hold the squat position for the desired amount of time, keeping the weight plate steady and your core engaged.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-plate-squat-hold-front_LrtgCLV.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-plate-squat-hold-side_mxmbCnO.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Plate Thruster', 'Start with the plate at chest height. Begin a squat.
Make sure to hit parallel depth. On your way back up, use the momentum you generate with your legs to help push the plate into an overhead position.
Let the plate return to chest height before initiating the next squat.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-plate-squat-thruster-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-plate-squat-thruster-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Dumbbell Overhead Squat', 'Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder-width apart and hold two dumbbells overhead with both hands, using an overhand grip.
