Lower your body as far as you can while keeping the dumbbells overhead, then push back up to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of repetitions, making sure to keep your back straight, chest lifted, and the dumbbells stable overhead throughout the entire movement.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-dumbbell-overhead-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-dumbbell-overhead-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Single Arm Overhead Squat', 'Stand with your feet shoulder-width apart and a dumbbell in your right hand, extending it overhead.
Inhale and begin to squat down, keeping the dumbbell overhead and your back straight.
Go down as far as you can while still maintaining control, then exhale and return to standing position, keeping the dumbbell overhead. Repeat for desired reps and then switch to the other arm.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-dumbbell-single-arm-overhead-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-dumbbell-single-arm-overhead-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Curtsy Lunge', 'Stand facing away from the anchor point, holding onto the TRX handles with both hands.
Step your left foot behind your right, crossing it behind your right leg, and lower yourself into a curtsy lunge.
Push through your right foot to return to the starting position and repeat the movement with the other leg.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-curtsy-lunge-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-curtsy-lunge-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Jumping Squat', 'Stand facing the TRX straps and place your feet shoulder-width apart.
Begin by lowering into a squat position by bending at the knees and hips, keeping your back straight and chest up.
Explosively jump up off the ground, using your arms for momentum if desired.
Land softly back in the squat position, making sure to absorb the impact with your legs.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-jump-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-jump-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Lateral Lunge', 'Grasp the TRX handles with both hands and extend your arms straight in front of you.
Step laterally to one side, keeping your arms extended and your core engaged.
Lower your body into a lunge position, keeping your front knee bent at a 90-degree angle and your back leg straight.
Push off your front foot to return to the starting position, keeping your arms extended and your core engaged.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-lateral-lunge-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-lateral-lunge-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Reverse Lunge', 'Hold on to the TRX straps and step away until the strap is taut.
Step backwards with one leg in to a lunge position and gently tap your knee to the floor.
Lunge back to the starting position and repeat with the other leg.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-reverse-lunge-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-reverse-lunge-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Split Squat', 'Hold the two TRX straps and step away until the straps are taut. Take a split stance.
Bring your back knee to the floor and gently tap the floor.
Use your arms and the TRX to help assist you getting back into the starting position.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-split-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-split-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('TRX Squat', 'Hold the two TRX straps and lean away from the anchor point.
Flex at the hips and knees in to a squat position.
You can use your arms and the straps to assist you back into the starting position.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-squat-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-trx-squat-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Chair Pose', 'Stand straight with your feet hip-width apart and arms at your sides.
Inhale and raise your arms straight up over your head.
Exhale and bend your knees, lowering your hips as if you were sitting in a chair.
Hold the pose for a few breaths, then inhale and stand up straight.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-chair-pose-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-chair-pose-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Crescent Moon Pose', 'Begin in Runners Lunge pose with your right foot forward.
Slowly lift your torso up and bring your arms overhead, palms facing each other.
Make sure your right knee is directly above your ankle, and your left leg is straight behind you.
Hold for a few breaths before repeating on the other side.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch', 'Begin in Crescent Moon Pose with your right foot forward and a block nearby.
Place the block at the highest height under your left hand.
Reach your left arm behind you and take hold of your left foot or ankle.
Gently pull your foot towards your buttocks while pressing your left hand into the block to deepen the stretch in your left quad. Hold for a few breaths before releasing and repeating on the other side.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-quad-stretch-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-quad-stretch-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Crescent Moon Pose Quad Stretch With Block', 'Begin in Crescent Moon Pose with your right foot forward and a block nearby.
Place the block at the highest height under your left hand.
Reach your left arm behind you and take hold of your left foot or ankle.
Gently pull your foot towards your buttocks while pressing your left hand into the block to deepen the stretch in your left quad. Hold for a few breaths before releasing and repeating on the other side.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-quad-stretch-with-block-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-crescent-moon-pose-quad-stretch-with-block-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Lord Of The Dance', 'Begin by standing tall with your feet hip-width apart.
Shift your weight onto your left foot and bring your right heel towards your glute.
Reach your right arm back and grab onto the inside of your right foot or ankle.
Inhale and lift your right foot away from your glute while extending your left arm forward. Hold for 5-10 breaths before switching sides.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-lord-of-the-dance-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-lord-of-the-dance-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Monkey Pose', 'Begin in a low lunge with your right foot forward and your left knee on the ground.
Slowly slide your left knee back while extending your right leg forward, keeping both legs straight.
Lower your body down to the ground, using your hands for support if needed.
Hold the pose for a few breaths, then switch sides and repeat.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-monkey-pose-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-monkey-pose-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Whoops! - 404', '', 'quads', '{}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Runners Lunge', 'Begin in Downward Facing Dog pose (Adho Mukha Svanasana).
Step your right foot forward between your hands.
Place your left knee on the ground behind you and slide it back until you feel a stretch in your left hip flexor.
Keep your hands on the ground or lift them to the sky and hold for a few breaths before repeating on the other side.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-runners-lunge-front.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-yoga-runners-lunge-side.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Alternating Lunge And Twist', 'Set up the landmine attachment and load weight.
Stand facing the landmine, holding the weight away from your chest.
Step backward with one leg, lunge down while twisting your torso toward the front leg, return to starting position, and repeat on the other side.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-alternating-lunge-and-twist-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-alternating-lunge-and-twist-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Alternating Lunge To Chest Press', 'Stand facing the landmine with feet hip-width apart and holding the end of the landmine barbell with both hands, keeping elbows bent and close to your body.
Step backward with the right foot, lunge down, and press the landmine away from your chest.
Push through the left heel to return to the starting position while pulling the landmine back to your chest.
Repeat on the opposite side, alternating for the desired number of reps.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-alternating-lunge-to-chest-press-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-alternating-lunge-to-chest-press-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Curtsy Lunge', 'Stand facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar at your side with one hand.
With the leg on the same side of your body as the barbell, lunge backward and across your body at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to lower your back knee gently to the ground.
Drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position, and repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-curtsy-lunge-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-curtsy-lunge-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Goblet Curtsy Lunge', 'Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar in the goblet position in front of your chest with your elbows close to your sides.
Step backward and across your body with one leg at a 45 degree angle while keeping your weight on your front heel to gently lower your back knee to the ground.
Drive through your front heel as you step back up and to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching legs.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-goblet-curtsy-lunge-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-goblet-curtsy-lunge-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Goblet Lateral Lunge', 'Start facing the barbell while holding the end of the bar close to your chest in the goblet position with your elbows tucked in close to your body.
Step directly out to the side with both toes pointing forward. Keep your weight on the heel of the leg you step out with as you sink down over that foot while your other leg remains straight for balance.
Drive through the heel over which you have centered your body as you step back to the starting position.
Repeat for the desired number of reps before switching sides.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-goblet-lateral-lunge-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-goblet-lateral-lunge-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Hack Squat', 'Start facing away from the landmine attachment with the end of the barbell resting on one shoulder against the base of your neck while leaning slightly back into the weight of the barbell.
Squat down with control while keeping the weight of the barbell as close to centered over your midpoint as possible, then drive through your heels to stand all the way back up and return to starting position.
Repeat for desired number of reps, then switch the side of your body the barbell is on every subsequent set.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-hack-squat-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-hack-squat-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Lateral Lunge', 'Stand facing the landmine with your feet shoulder width apart while holding the end of the barbell in your hands with your arms fully extended down towards the ground.
While keeping your torso tall and core engaged, step directly out to one side, using the foot you have stepped out with to sit down into the lunge while keeping your other leg straight.
Drive through your heel on your bent leg as your step together to return to the starting position.
Repeat for desired number of reps on the same side before switching sides.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-lateral-lunge-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-lateral-lunge-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Lunge', 'Stand in front of the landmine with your feet hip-width apart and your back straight. Grasp the landmine barbell with one hand, holding it at at your side with your palm facing in towards your leg.
Take a step backward with your foot on the same side that youre holding the barbell, lowering your body into a lunge position. Bend both knees to lower your body down until your front thigh is parallel to the ground, or as low as your flexibility allows. Keep your torso upright, your chest lifted, and your core engaged throughout the movement.
Push through the heel of your front foot to return to the starting position. Repeat for desired number of reps before switching sides.', 'quads', '{https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-lunge-side.mp4,https://media.musclewiki.com/media/uploads/videos/branded/male-Barbell-landmine-lunge-front.mp4}') ON CONFLICT(name) DO NOTHING;INSERT INTO exercise (name, description, category, videos) VALUES('Landmine Lunge To Overhead Press', 'Stand facing the landmine attachment while holding the end of the bar with one hand at your shoulder on the same side with your elbow tucked to your body underneath your wrist.
Step back with the leg on the same side that you are holding the bar on and with control lower yourself down into a lunge position while keeping your core engaged and torso tall, then drive through your front heel as you step back to the starting position.
Once your feet are back in the starting position, drive the bar up overhead until your arm is fully extended, then lower the bar back down to the starting position.
